<para xml:id="C28.S1.p7">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="58" xml:id="C28.S1.p7.s1">
Alternative notations for the functions are as follows.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C28.S1.Px1">
<title>Arscott (1964b) and McLachlan (1947)</title>  
     
<para xml:id="C28.S1.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="59" xml:id="C28.S1.Px1.p1.s1">
 <Math mode="display" xml:id="C28.S1.EGx3">\mathrm{Fey}_{n}(z,q)=\sqrt{\tfrac{1}{2}\pi}g_{\mathit{e},n}(h)\mathrm{ce}_{n} \left(0,q\right){\mathrm{Mc}^{(2)}_{n}}\left(z,h\right),\mathrm{Me}_{n}^{(1,2)}(z,q)=\sqrt{\tfrac{1}{2}\pi}g_{\mathit{e},n}(h)\mathrm{ ce}_{n}\left(0,q\right){\mathrm{Mc}^{(3,4)}_{n}}\left(z,h\right),\mathrm{Gey}_{n}(z,q)=\sqrt{\tfrac{1}{2}\pi}g_{\mathit{o},n}(h)\mathrm{se}_{n} '\left(0,q\right){\mathrm{Ms}^{(2)}_{n}}\left(z,h\right),\mathrm{Ne}_{n}^{(1,2)}(z,q)=\sqrt{\tfrac{1}{2}\pi}g_{\mathit{o},n}(h)\mathrm{ se}_{n}'\left(0,q\right){\mathrm{Ms}^{(3,4)}_{n}}\left(z,h\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="60" xml:id="C28.S1.Px1.p1.s2">
Arscott (1964b) also uses <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S1.Px1.p1.m1">-\mathrm{i}\mu</Math> for <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S1.Px1.p1.m2">\nu</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</paragraph>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C28.S1.Px2">
<title>Campbell (1955)</title>         
<para xml:id="C28.S1.Px2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="61" xml:id="C28.S1.Px2.p1.s1">
 <Math mode="display" xml:id="C28.Sx2.EGx1">\displaystyle\mathrm{in}_{n}=\mathrm{fe}_{n}, \displaystyle\mathrm{ceh}_{n}=\mathrm{Ce}_{n}, \displaystyle\mathrm{inh}_{n}=\mathrm{Fe}_{n},\displaystyle\mathrm{jn}_{n}=\mathrm{ge}_{n}, \displaystyle\mathrm{seh}_{n}=\mathrm{Se}_{n}, \displaystyle\mathrm{jnh}_{n}=\mathrm{Ge}_{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C28.S1.Px3">
<title>Abramowitz and Stegun (1964, Chapter 20)</title>    
<para xml:id="C28.S1.Px3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="62" xml:id="C28.S1.Px3.p1.s1">
 <Math mode="display" xml:id="C28.S1.Ex14">F_{\nu}(z)=\mathrm{Me}_{\nu}\left(z,q\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C28.S1.Px4">
<title>National Bureau of Standards (1967)</title>           
<para xml:id="C28.S1.Px4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="63" xml:id="C28.S1.Px4.p1.s1">
With <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S1.Px4.p1.m1">s=4q</Math> , <Math mode="display" xml:id="C28.S1.EGx4">\mathrm{Se}_{n}(s,z)=\dfrac{\mathrm{ce}_{n}\left(z,q\right)}{\mathrm{ce}_{n} \left(0,q\right)},\mathrm{So}_{n}(s,z)=\dfrac{\mathrm{se}_{n}\left(z,q\right)}{\mathrm{se}_{n}' \left(0,q\right)}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C28.S1.Px5">
<title>Stratton et al. (1941)</title>  
         
<para xml:id="C28.S1.Px5.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="64" xml:id="C28.S1.Px5.p1.s1">
With <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S1.Px5.p1.m1">c=2\sqrt{q}</Math> , <Math mode="display" xml:id="C28.S1.EGx5">\mathrm{Se}_{n}(c,z)=\dfrac{\mathrm{ce}_{n}\left(z,q\right)}{\mathrm{ce}_{n} \left(0,q\right)},\mathrm{So}_{n}(c,z)=\dfrac{\mathrm{se}_{n}\left(z,q\right)}{\mathrm{se}_{n}' \left(0,q\right)}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C28.S1.Px6">
<title>Zhang and Jin (1996)</title>   
<para xml:id="C28.S1.Px6.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="65" xml:id="C28.S1.Px6.p1.s1">
The radial functions <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S1.Px6.p1.m1">{\mathrm{Mc}^{(j)}_{n}}\left(z,h\right)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S1.Px6.p1.m2">{\mathrm{Ms}^{(j)}_{n}}\left(z,h\right)</Math> are denoted by <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S1.Px6.p1.m3">{\mathrm{Mc}^{(j)}_{n}}\left(z,q\right)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S1.Px6.p1.m4">{\mathrm{Ms}^{(j)}_{n}}\left(z,q\right)</Math> ,respectively.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
